  abstract = {In this paper, we study the local geometry at a prime p of a certain class of (PEL) type Shimura varieties. We begin by studing the Newton polygon stratification of the special fiber of a Shimura variety with good reduction at p. Each stratum can be described in terms of the products of the reduced fiber of the corresponding RapoportZink space with some smooth varieties (we call the Igusa varieties), and of the action on them of a certain p-adic group T{$\alpha$}, which depends on the stratum. (The definition of the Igusa varieties in this context is based upon a result of Zink on the slope filtration of a Barsotti-Tate group and on the notion of Oort's foliation.) In particular, we show that it is possible to compute the e\textasciiacute tale cohomology with compact supports of the Newton polygon strata, in terms of the e\textasciiacute tale cohomology with compact supports of the Igusa varieties and the Rapoport-Zink spaces, and of the group homology of T{$\alpha$}. Further more, we are able to extend Zariski locally the above constructions to characteristic zero and obtain an analoguous description for the \textasciiacute etale cohomology of the Shimura varieties in both the cases of good and bad reduction at p. As a result of this analysis, we obtain a description of the l-adic cohomology of the Shimura varieties, in terms of the l-adic cohomology with compact supports of the Igusa varieties and of the Rapoport-Zink spaces.},
  langid = {english},
  file = {/Users/rumi-park/Zotero/storage/V2KMNNEJ/Mantovan - ON CERTAIN UNITARY GROUP SHIMURA VARIETIES.pdf}
}

